The House Committee on Judiciary offers the following substitute to SB 173:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 3 of Chapter 11 of Title 9 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to pleadings and motions, so as to authorize movants to file notices of uncontested
3 motions in superior courts and state courts; to provide for uncontested motions to be deemed
4 granted and entered; to provide for review by chief judge of any judge with two uncontested
5 motions deemed granted on his or her docket; to provide for management reports regarding
6 each such review; to provide for statutory construction; to require that parties to a case
7 provide a copy of filed motions or notices to the judge assigned to such case; to provide for
8 instructions on how to provide such copies; to provide for related matters; to repeal
9 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
11 SECTION 1.
12 Article 3 of Chapter 11 of Title 9 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
13 pleadings and motions, is amended by adding new Code sections to read as follows:
14 "9-11-16.1.
15 (a) In the event that a superior court judge or a state court judge fails to rule upon a
16 properly served pretrial motion before him or her to which no objection has been filed by
