17 any party or any valid intervenor within 60 days of the filing of such motion, the moving
18 party may file a notice of uncontested motion with such judge.
19 (b) Should a judge continue to fail to rule upon a motion before him or her within seven
20 days of the filing of a notice of uncontested motion pursuant to subsection (a) of this Code
21 section, such motion shall thereafter be deemed granted and entered.
22 (c) The operation of subsection (a) or (b) of this Code section shall be tolled during any
23 period that a hearing on the motion is scheduled until the day after such hearing is held.
24 (d) In the event that a judge has a motion deemed granted and entered pursuant to
25 subsection (b) of this Code section in two or more cases before such judge within two
26 years, the chief judge of the court at issue may conduct a review of the docket management
27 techniques and procedures of such judge and may issue a report of his or her findings.
28 (e) Nothing in this Code section shall prohibit any court from conducting any review of
29 its own operations of its own initiative.
30 9-11-16.2.
31 (a) Whenever a party to a case files a motion or notice with a court in this state pursuant
32 to the provisions of this chapter, the party shall cause a copy of such motion or notice to
33 be provided to the judge assigned to the case in which such motion or notice is filed or to
34 another designee as identified by such judge.
35 (b) Each judge of a court in which the provisions of this chapter apply shall, by the
36 issuance of a standing order or any other manner, provide instructions on how parties to
37 any case before such judge can provide copies of filed motions or notices to such judge
38 pursuant to the provisions of subsection (a) of this Code section."
39 SECTION 2.
40 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
